body: You are right, those tests are now relics of the previous implementation (i.e. when the `OperationHelper` was present) and don't make any sense now, I'll remove them. But I admit that I used this test class to prove that the generated primitive ops will work flawlessly, which is not the goal of a unit test so I'll clean that up...
